The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 National Thermal Power Corporation Ltds (NTPC) net profit after tax increased 18.65 per cent to Rs 1,552.80 crore for the quarter ended June 30 from Rs 1,308.7 crore in the same period in the previous fiscal. Total income has increased 17.86 per cent to Rs 7,790.5 crore for the reporting quarter from Rs 6,609.5 crore in the year-ago period, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. 

 Polaris Software Labs net profit rose to Rs 17.48 crore for the quarter ended June 30 from Rs 7.95 crore a year ago. Total income increased 7.22 per cent to Rs 189.60 crore from Rs 176.83 crore. The group has posted a consolidated profit after tax of Rs 20.27 crore for the quarter compared with Rs 11.62 crore a year ago. 

 Hindustan Construction Companys (HCC) profit after tax in the first quarter of the current fiscal was Rs 25.12 crore against Rs 22.66 crore a year ago, a 10.87 per cent rise. The companys turnover rose 21.11 per cent to Rs 580.62 crore from Rs 479.43 crore a year ago. 

 Alps Industries Ltds net profit was Rs.7.12 crore in the first quarter of the current fiscal against Rs 4.51 crore a year ago. Turnover was Rs 93.11 crore compared with Rs 51.90 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year, an increase of 79.40 per cent. 

 Neyveli Lignite Corporations net profit declined 43.33 per cent to Rs 223.84 crore for the quarter ended June 30 from Rs 395.01 crore a year ago. Total income decreased 20.09 per cent to Rs 761.01 crore from Rs 952.39 crore. 

 Sterlite Industries (India) Ltds net profit for the quarter ended June 30 was Rs 1,220.91 crore against Rs 228.22 crore a year ago. Turnover increased 142 per cent to Rs 5,001.87 crore from Rs 2,058.89 crore. 

 Bharat Earth Movers Ltds (BEML) net profit rose 20.95 per cent to Rs 15.01 crore for the quarter ended June 30 from Rs 12.41 crore a year ago. Total income (net of excise) decreased 10.19 per cent to Rs 343.76 crore from Rs 382.79 crore in the same quarter last year. 

 Kalpataru Power Transmissions profit after tax was Rs 29 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 9.4 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year. Profit before tax was Rs 40.2 crore compared with Rs 13.6 crore a year ago. 

 Hindustan Sanitaryware and Industries (HSIL) net profit was Rs 7.65 crore against Rs 4.37 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal. Gross sales increased 37 per cent to Rs 128.36 crore from Rs 93.66 crore a year ago. 

